<br>
There are so many variables to set and test that it's taken me 2 days to get as far as I have.<br>
<br>
I didn't know it, but UT2003 does have driver issues with the Radeon. And stupid me was using that as a test to see if it would lock up.<br>
<br>
I finally ran 3 successful tests with it without 1 lock up. Here's what I did:<br>
<br>
System (to recap):<br>
Abit Vp6 Motherboard, Via chipset<br>
2 P3 1Ghz (not overclocked anymore *sigh*)<br>
1GB Ram<br>
Radeon 9700 Pro<br>
SB Live Value (soon to be upgraded to Audigy -ugh, another nightmare? hope not!)<br>
<br>
1. Updated to latest BIOS I could find <br>
2. Installed fresh copy of XP<br>
3. Installed Service Pack 1<br>
4. Installed all updates from Windows<br>
5. Installed latest released Via 4n1 Drivers (440)<br>
6. Installed the .6178 Catalyst Drivers from ATI<br>
    (The latest driver on their site are .6166, I found the .6718 drivers under a help forum for a fix with lockups during games)<br>
7. Went to display properties and took down Graphics Acceleration 2 notches.<br>
8. Prayed<br>
9. Ran thru 3 demos of UT2003 - no lockups and by Cazic did it look GREAT!<br>
<br>
Then I turned on 4x Anti Aliasing and 8x ansitropic filtering (or what ever it's called. I'm so brain dead now) and it looks even better! with no reduction in frame rate!<br>
<br>
I'm in awe. Installing EQ and next and going to stand in the bazaar with clip plane out and spell effects on and see how long it will last.<br>
<br>
*crosses fingers*<br>
<br>
So after seeing what this card can actually do, I'm saying &quot;I only paid $350 for this??! Whata bargain!&quot; <p><center>When in doubt, feign and let the others die.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8204">Magelo Profile</a></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uskahld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>skahld</A> at: 10/9/02 10:25:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucorasik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corasik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/10/02 2:55:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1606.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video card decision</span><hr size=1> Nvidia bring out new cards every 6 months, It will be interesting to see what they do to compete with the new ATI =)<br>
